      "message": "\u003e We can turn it into a computed value, but computed value will only be cached when accessed by an observer. however will be used during actions (non-observer), so using @observable is better than @computed.\n\nhm, sorry, i still don\u0027t understand. We do use @computed in L86 in ps8. Doesn\u0027t this contract what you say?\n\nwhy doesn\u0027t the following work:\n1) add a test to this._tests only if nextSeg \u003d\u003d\u003d undefined\n2)\n\n  @computed get tests(): readonly ReadonlyTest[] { \n    const ret \u003d [];\n\n    function dfs(n: TestNode) {\n      ret.Array.prototype.push.apply(ret, n._tests);\n      n.unelidedChildren.forEach(dfs);\n    }\n\n    dfs(this);\n    return ret; \n  }\n\njust to be clear: my concern here is that this has O(tests * depth) space complexity, and we are using only a tiny bit of it. I.e. we are precomputing all-tests in each node, but in practice the user would click only on few.",
